## Get Status By Handler

<%= partial "includes/APIReference/Lending/Examples/get_status_by_handler.tmpl.erb" %>

Retrieves status of a newly created loan

<aside class="success">Pro Tip: For best results, poll this API no more frequently than every 1000ms.</aside>

### HTTP Request

<img src="images/get.png" alt="get" class="http_verb"/> <api>`https://api.example.com/v1/lending/loans/status?handlerId=<value>`</api>

### Query Parameters

Parameter | Use | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
handlerId | required | The identifier from the results of the loan creation request

### Response Properties

Property | Description | Notes
--------- | ------- | -------
status | The status of the loan creation request | One of: <em>PENDING</em>, <em>OPEN</em>, <em>CLOSING</em>, <em>CLOSED</em>, or <em>FAILED</em>
reason | Detailed explanation for the status | Set only when status is not <em>OPEN</em> or <em>CLOSED</em>
<em>all others</em> | Properties of the newly created loan | Set only when status is <em>OPEN</em> or <em>CLOSED</em>

### Response Codes
HTTP Code | Status
--------- | ------- 
<code class="level200">200</code> | OK
<code class="level400">404</code> | Not Found
